Tianjin Labor Market Provides Job Opportunities
TIANJIN , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Tianjin Municipality , the largest port city in north China , has established a labor market network to find new job opportunities for unemployeed workers .
The network , which includes 60 labor centers and 1,600 branches in counties and districts , found jobs for more than 150,000 laid-off workers during 1997 .
Most centers have installed computers which provide information concerning job opportunities across the city .
The labor centers also provided services for some 20,000 enterprises last year .
